{"title": "Burning Wheel", "description": "Though Aldous Huxley is best known for his later novels and essays, he started his writing career as a poet. The Burning Wheel is his first work, a collection of thirty poems that pay homage in style to poets who wrote in the Romantic or the French symbolist styles. Many of the poems deal with themes of light, darkness, sight, music, art, war, and idealism vs. realism. Though the optimism in his early works waned as he became older, his characteristically optimistic and determined point of view shines through.  - Summary by Mary Kay<br>\nThe last poem was read collaboratively by ezwa, AlgyPug and Larry Wilson.", "duration": 2816, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1538", "name": "Aldous Huxley"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox/burning_wheel_1505.jpg", "copyright_year": "1916", "genres": ["Single author"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mary Kay"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Availle"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Burning Wheel", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox/burningwheel_01_huxley_64kb.mp3", "duration": 133}, {"section": 2, "title": "Doors of the Temple", "readers": [9984], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox/burningwheel_02_huxley_64kb.mp3", "duration": 69}, {"section": 3, "title": "Villiers de L'Isle-Adam", "readers": [4705], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox/burningwheel_03_huxley_64kb.mp3", "duration": 68}, {"section": 4, "title": "Darkness", "readers": [9902], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox/burningwheel_04_huxley_64kb.mp3", "duration": 57}, {"section": 5, "title": "Mole", "readers": [4705], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/burning_wheel_1505_librivox